<paragraph id="8BBC36FD6A75784AFF4B546AB9148ECE" blockId="1.[151,1436,1651,2001]" box="[151,288,1651,1677]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36FD6A75784AFF1A5482BBFA8EF6" blockId="1.[151,1436,1651,2001]" box="[198,974,1691,1717]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
Male (
<figureCitation id="13382A786A75784AFECE5482B9B78EF6" box="[274,387,1691,1717]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 2" captionStartId="2.[151,269,701,725]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,181,675]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[154,1451,177,675]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 2. Idmon flavata sp. nov. (Scale = 10 mm) 1. Dorasal view, 2. Ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273822/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
Figs. 
<number id="3DCB24DA6A75784AFE895482B9B78EF6" box="[341,387,1691,1717]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Forewing length 
<quantity id="4CFB9B186A75784AFDBD5482BA828EF6" box="[609,694,1691,1717]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" unit="mm" value="17.0">17 mm</quantity>
, antenna length 
<quantity id="4CFB9B186A75784AFCA95482BBFD8EF6" box="[885,969,1691,1717]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36FD6A75784AFF4B54DAB8F08F6E" blockId="1.[151,1436,1651,2001]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
Antennae dark brown, longer than 
<number id="3DCB24DA6A75784AFDEB54DABA758E9E" box="[567,577,1731,1757]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DCB24DA6A75784AFD9054DABA688E9E" box="[588,604,1731,1757]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="2.0">2</number>
of forewing costa, club yellow ventrally; palpi second segment erect, densely covered with long greyish white scales ventrally, third segment long and slender, distinctly protruding.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36FD6A75784AFF1A5522BB168F8E" blockId="1.[151,1436,1651,2001]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
Wings upper surface with ground color dark brown, unmarked, cilia grey, without secondary sexual characters. Forewing underside ground color the same as that of upper surface, covered with yellow scales at apex and the end of cell. Hindwing underside yellow, costa and termen brown, veins yellow, with small black spots in the spaces Cu 
<number id="3DCB24DA6A75784AFE8A55DAB96A8F92" box="[342,350,1987,2001]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="2.0">2</number>
to Rs, the one in space Sc+R 
<number id="3DCB24DA6A75784AFD6A55DABA8A8F92" box="[694,702,1987,2001]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1.0">1</number>
blurred.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF7C66756A767849FF4B50A4BC668A96" box="[151,1106,701,725]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273822/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" targetBox="[154,1436,181,675]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8BBC36FD6A767849FF4B50A4BC668A96" blockId="2.[151,1106,701,725]" box="[151,1106,701,725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B977EAEF6A767849FF4B50A4B9768A96" bold="true" box="[151,322,701,725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">FIGURES 1–2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C034D7E6A767849FE9550A7B9EA8A96" box="[329,478,702,725]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Idmon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B977EAEF6A767849FE9550A7B9EA8A96" box="[329,478,702,725]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Idmon flavata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24457946A767849FE3950A7BA038A96" box="[485,567,702,725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(Scale = 10 mm) 1. Dorasal view, 2. Ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BBC36FD6A767849FF1A5110B9E48C50" blockId="2.[151,1437,777,1043]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13382A786A767849FE5D5110B9C18B60" box="[385,501,777,803]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1741,1765]" captionTargetBox="[248,1311,1189,1694]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[232,1355,1142,1715]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 7. Male genitalia of Idmon flavata sp. nov. 3. ring, lateral view, 4. tegumen, dorsal view, 5. valva, inner view, 6. aedeagus, 7. juxta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273823/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
Figs. 
<number id="3DCB24DA6A767849FE195110B9C18B60" box="[453,501,777,803]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="5.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="3.0">3–7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Uncus long, about twice longer than tegumen, deeply bifid at half distal portion, its two arms long and thin, running slightly outwardly; socius absent; gnathos well developed, elbowshaped, membranous and separated each other at tip; saccus rather long; valva simple, broad, with the distal upper portion shallowly bifid, forming the ampullar and the harpal processes, the ampullar process with upper margin slightly swelled, the harpal process with lower margin obviously convex, outer margin arched; aedeagus with subzonal sheath nearly as long as suprazonal sheath, and bifurcated distally; juxta U-shaped with lateral arms curved inwardly.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF7C66756A767849FF4B54D4B9838F44" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273823/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" targetBox="[248,1311,1189,1694]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8BBC36FD6A767849FF4B54D4B9838F44" blockId="2.[151,1436,1741,1799]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B977EAEF6A767849FF4B54D4B9718EA6" bold="true" box="[151,325,1741,1765]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">FIGURES 3–7.</emphasis>
Male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D7E6A767849FDD354D7BA928EA6" box="[527,678,1742,1765]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Idmon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B977EAEF6A767849FDD354D7BA928EA6" box="[527,678,1742,1765]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Idmon flavata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24457946A767849FD7254D4BB378EA7" box="[686,771,1741,1764]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
3. ring, lateral view, 4. tegumen, dorsal view, 5. valva, inner view, 6. aedeagus, 7. juxta.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BBC36FD6A767849FF4B5522B8C08F16" blockId="2.[151,1436,1851,2001]" box="[151,244,1851,1877]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Remark</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36FD6A767848FF1A557AB9688899" blockId="2.[151,1436,1851,2001]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,152,218]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
The new species strikingly resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D7E6A767849FD50557ABC458F3E" authority="Chou &amp; Huang, 1994" authorityName="Chou &amp; Huang" authorityYear="1994" box="[652,1137,1891,1917]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Idmon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujianana">
<emphasis id="B977EAEF6A767849FD50557ABB648F3F" box="[652,848,1891,1916]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Idmon fujianana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B0C6A767849FCBD557ABC5C8F3E" author="Chou" box="[865,1128,1891,1917]" pageId="2" pageNumber="62" refString="Chou, I. (ed.) (1994) Monographia Rhopalocerorum Sinensium. Henan Scientific and Technological Publishing House, Zhengzhou, 854 pp." type="book" year="1994">
Chou &amp; Huang, 
<number id="3DCB24DA6A767849FBF6557ABC5C8F3E" box="[1066,1128,1891,1917]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but can be easily distinguished by hindwing underside densely covered with yellow scales, as well as the clearly defined small black spots in spaces Cu 
<number id="3DCB24DA6A767849FEAC55DAB94C8F92" box="[368,376,1987,2001]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="2.0">2</number>
to Rs, the one in space Sc+R 
<number id="3DCB24DA6A767849FD0955DABAE98F92" box="[725,733,1987,2001]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1.0">1</number>
indistinct; uncus with the two lateral arms not parallel each other; valva with the ampullar and harpal processes hardly connected at apex; juxta U-shaped with lateral arm curved inwardly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
